{
  "stem": "15721.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And therefore, out of the 570,000 or so Jews that there were in Germany, eventually I think better than 300,000 were able to escape by way of emigration.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And only a minor fraction of the total German Jewish community was exterminated in the camps later.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was different, let's say, with the French Jewry or Dutch Jewry or, of course, Eastern European Jewry, where the death rate was close to 100%.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was due to the fact that they had time-- this was still before the Second World War, which broke out on September 1st, 1939-- so there were virtually six and a half years before the outbreak of the war which made emigration much more difficult thereafter.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The German Jews had the opportunity, especially if they had friends or had the kind of professions or capacities that other countries were willing to welcome, to leave.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And therefore, to-- to suggest to my parents that they should emigrate was perfectly rational from my point of view.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In fact, it was necessary.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was just that my father was such a patriot and so stubborn.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The fact that they finally emigrated was due to the fact that my father was taken to Dachau concentration camp in Kristallnacht on November 9th, 1938, and then was told that they would release him only when he could prove by a visa and-- and ticket that he had made final arrangements for emigration from Germany.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was functioning as the hazzan at the- one of my buddies' wedding and I was standing under the chuppah when somebody handed me a cable that my mother had sent saying, father in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Rescue him.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Signed, Mother.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
